Using the beginning equity, the formula to determine the sustainable growth rate will be modified as follows.
&nbsp;
$$\text{Sustainable Growth Rate}=\text{Return on Equity}\times\text{Retention Ratio}\times 100$$

Now we will substitute equity at the beginning of the period into obtained equation from step 8 in the following way:

$$\begin{align*}
\text{SGR}&=\dfrac{\text{NI}\cdot\text{b}}{\text{TE}_{\text{b}}}\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\text{NI}}{\text{TE}_{\text{b}}}\cdot\text{b}
\end{align*}$$

Since we know from step 6 that the return on equity at the beginning of the period is equal to net income and total equity at the beginning of the period, we get that formula for sustainable growth rate is:
$$\begin{align*}
\text{SGR}=\text{ROE}_{b}\cdot\text{b}
\end{align*}$$

In conclusion, the sustainable growth rate equation where ROE is based on beginning of period equity is presented and proven.

Since we know from step 7 that the return on assets at the beginning of the period is equal to net income and total assets at the beginning of the period, we get that formula for sustainable growth rate is:
$$\begin{align*}
\text{SGR}=\text{ROA}_{b}\cdot\text{b}
\end{align*}$$

In conclusion, another version of the sustainable growth rate equation based on the internal growth rate formula is presented and proven.
